  <static seed="92" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>Maygen is participating in a running event. In the first hour, she completed <m>{{\frac{1}{5}}}</m> of the total distance. After another hour, in total she had completed <m>{{\frac{11}{30}}}</m> of the total distance.</p>
<p>What fraction of the total distance did Maygen complete during the second hour?</p>
<p>Maygen completed <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of the distance during the second hour.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{6}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is a subtraction problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{11}{30}}} - {{\frac{1}{5}}} 
      \amp = \frac{11}{30}-\frac{1 \cdot 6}{5 \cdot 6} \\
      \amp = \frac{11}{30} - \frac{6}{30} \\
      \amp = \frac{11-6}{30} \\
      \amp = \frac{5}{30} \\
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{6}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Maygen completed <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of the distance during the second hour.</p>
</solution>
